The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) yesterday detained the Director-General of the Voice of Nigeria (VON), Osita Okechukwu, over alleged misappropriation of public funds.   Amid probe, Abba Kyari makes first public appearance at IGP…     APC chair: Governors in the dark as Buhari keeps party…     Outrage as four teenagers kill girl, burn head for money…   Okechukwu drove to the EFCC headquarters in Abuja at about 1:30 pm to honour an invitation from the agency over allegations of conspiracy, abuse of office and misappropriation of public funds to the tune of N1.3 billion. Spokesperson for EFCC, Wilson Uwujaren, confirmed the VON DG’s invitation but gave no details.